            "rationale": "Reviewer's F12 flagged the cco: -> https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ binding and the unverified 'verified against CCO v1.7' claim as an NFR-013 risk. Critic refined the framing: JSON-LD prefix expansion is byte-deterministic across implementations once @context is fixed, so NFR-013 itself is not at risk from CCO release drift. The real risk is realist anchoring \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the dereferenceable identity of the expanded IRI depends on what CCO actually publishes, and the spec ships no in-repo golden file, no DECISIONS.md ADR, and no test pinning the assertion. Merged into one issue with critic's framing: severity remains major (linked-data integrity, not byte determinism); fix requires pinning a CCO version in DECISIONS.md with a citable artifact AND a golden-file expansion test for the cited class IRIs.",
            "trace": {
