          },
          {
            "id": "I19",
            "title": "ecm:contentHash plays two contradictory roles (informational on ImportedOntology vs load-bearing on Serialization) without subject-type-conditioned semantics",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "accept_reviewer",
            "severity": "advisory",
            "rationale": "Reviewer's F19 cited sec 5.6:436 (ImportedOntology ecm:contentHash field), sec 12.4:977 ('informational only; not used as an integrity check on load'), sec 5.15:660 (Required on Serialization), sec 19:1399 (load-bearing for the realist-anchored manifest). Critic confirmed: same predicate IRI, contradictory normative force depending on subject type; validators cannot uniformly enforce. Fix is either to split into ecm:ontologyContentHash (informational) and ecm:serializationContentHash (normative), or to declare the dual role with subject-type-conditioned rules in sec 5.2.",
            "trace": {
              "reviewer_finding_id": "F19",
