          },
          {
            "id": "I2",
            "title": "OED-303 (validation report retention) is deferred to Phase 3 but its decision constrains Phase 1 golden files \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a circular dependency",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "accept_reviewer",
            "severity": "major",
            "rationale": "Phase 1 delivers the canonical serializer and the structural validator (FR-C001), both of which write to ecm:validationReports (SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.4, \u00c2\u00a75.13). Phase 1 golden files will capture a particular state of ecm:validationReports at the time they are committed. OED-303, deferred to Phase 3 Decisions Deferred, determines whether subsequent validation runs append to or replace the array. If 'latest only' is chosen in Phase 3, any Phase 1 golden file recording a multi-report state is rendered invalid; if 'one per save' is chosen, golden files committed assuming an empty or single-entry state break. The VMP shape is committed in Phase 1 but the policy governing array population is deferred three phases later. The critic confirmed this analysis and added that the dependency would only be relaxed if the ROADMAP explicitly stated Phase 1 golden files will contain an empty ecm:validationReports \u00e2\u20ac\u201d it does not. The source artifact confirms the deferred placement exactly as cited.",
            "trace": {
