            "rationale": "SPEC \u00c2\u00a717.4 lists exactly three info finding codes (LEGACY_DOCUMENT_MIGRATED, LEGACY_REALIST_ANCHOR_PLACEHOLDER, NORMALIZED_ON_SAVE) \u00e2\u20ac\u201d a closed enumeration. Phase 6 scope adds 'Modeling hints and early semantic-linter warnings beyond the \u00c2\u00a717 validator \u00e2\u20ac\u201d heuristics surfaced as info findings, not new hard errors.' No new codes are registered, no location in any schema catalog is named, no indication is given of whether these appear in ecm:validationReports (\u00c2\u00a75.13), and no interaction with \u00c2\u00a717.5 suppression (per-finding, per-target acknowledgement) is specified. The ValidationReport shape (\u00c2\u00a75.13) requires ecm:code, ecm:severity, ecm:target, and ecm:acknowledged on each finding, but Phase 6 specifies none of these for the new heuristic findings. The critic confirmed and reinforced: 'not new hard errors' only clarifies the severity floor; it does not bound the surface. The source artifact confirms the Phase 6 scope line verbatim.",
