            "severity": "minor",
            "rationale": "Phase 6 deliverables are starter examples, contextual help content, pattern-template gallery, modeling hints and semantic-linter warnings, pattern comparison spike, and DoD verification. None of these are bridging activities between edge-canonical surfaces. The label is inherited from SPEC \u00c2\u00a729 and is equally opaque there. A reader scanning the ROADMAP for 'where do starter examples ship?' or 'where does help content land?' will not locate Phase 6 by name. The critic confirmed this as a structural discoverability defect rather than a stylistic issue \u00e2\u20ac\u201d the phase name is the primary navigation anchor in a multi-phase document. Minor severity is confirmed as appropriate; the finding is self-contained and does not invalidate other phases.",
