          {
            "id": "I9",
            "title": "Cross-Cutting Commitments omit SPEC \u00c2\u00a710 (Versioning and Migration), leaving Phase 5 free to introduce new on-disk state without a mandated non-destructive migration obligation",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "accept_reviewer",
            "severity": "minor",
            "rationale": "SPEC \u00c2\u00a710 defines non-destructive migration, compatibility policy, and ecm:specVersion enforcement as cross-cutting invariants that apply to every phase touching canonical project state. Phase 5 introduces two new on-disk storage surfaces (IndexedDB and FSA folders), each requiring coordination with ecm:specVersion via a migration function, but neither the Cross-Cutting Commitments nor Phase 5 explicitly binds this work to \u00c2\u00a710.2/\u00c2\u00a710.3/\u00c2\u00a710.5. Phase 6 starter examples also introduce new canonical-v0.4 project files that must be migrable per policy. The absence means future ecm:specVersion bumps carry no mandated cross-cutting obligation in the ROADMAP. Phase 1 mentions legacy migration (v0.2\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.3\u00e2\u2020\u2019v0.4) but this is a one-time delivery, not a statement that the non-destructive migration policy is a continuing cross-cutting constraint. The critic confirmed without material extension.",
            "trace": {
              "reviewer_finding_id": "F9",
              "critic_verdict_id": "F9"
            }
          },
          {
            "id": "I10",
            "title": "Phase 2 FR-U028 acknowledgement-persistence question is unresolved and interacts with OED-303 in a way no phase claims ownership of",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "accept_reviewer",
            "severity": "minor",
            "rationale": "Phase 2 ships the validation report panel with per-finding acknowledgement (FR-U028, \u00c2\u00a717.5). SPEC \u00c2\u00a75.13 defines ecm:acknowledged as part of the canonical VMP shape, meaning acknowledgement state persists in the project document and must survive save/load. The ROADMAP does not specify where acknowledged state is written back to ecm:validationReports or what happens on save/reload. OED-303 (deferred to Phase 3) determines retention policy: if 'latest only' is chosen, a user who acknowledged a finding will lose that acknowledgement when the report is replaced on the next save. The ROADMAP does not flag this as a known limitation or require that OED-303 resolve this interaction before Phase 3 closes. No later phase claims the persistence design. The critic confirmed and added the specific OED-303 interaction, keeping minor severity.",
            "trace": {
              "reviewer_finding_id": "F10",
              "critic_verdict_id": "F10"
