          },
          {
            "id": "I11",
            "title": "IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md is referenced as the locus for all acceptance criteria and exit gates but is not a deliverable of any phase",
            "consensus": "both_agree",
            "resolution": "accept_reviewer",
            "severity": "minor",
            "rationale": "The ROADMAP's opening statement delegates per-task acceptance criteria, exit gates, and falsifiable test conditions to IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md. No phase lists authoring IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md as a deliverable. No cross-cutting commitment asserts it must exist before Phase 1 starts. This means Phase 1 could begin with only the ROADMAP's high-level scope bullets as its definition of done, which the critic confirmed are insufficiently falsifiable. The critic additionally noted that downstream artifacts \u00e2\u20ac\u201d synthesist documents, developer change proposals, Barcode audit history \u00e2\u20ac\u201d cannot reliably cross-reference criteria that do not exist in a versioned artifact. The source artifact confirms the dangling reference on line 7.",
