            "rationale": "I16 (major, critic-only): Phase 1 CLI scope declares 'export (all formats)' and 'import-ontology' as Phase 1 commands, but their underlying implementations are Phase 4 (ZIP packaging) and Phase 3 (Turtle term extraction) deliverables respectively. This is an intra-Phase-1 self-contradiction with no stub strategy, no error code, and no deferred-registration decision. The fix limits the Phase 1 export command to the formats whose implementations are delivered in Phase 1 and defers the stub strategy for the remaining commands to OED-307.",
            "before": "- Node CLI surface (\u00a723): validate, export (all formats), import-ontology, migrate, refactor-iri, with deterministic flags `--seed` / `--clock`, exit codes 0\u20134, and CLI path containment per \u00a712.2.",
            "after": "- Node CLI surface (\u00a723): validate, export (JSON-LD, Turtle, N-Triples, Mermaid, Markdown), migrate, refactor-iri, with deterministic flags `--seed` / `--clock`, exit codes 0\u20134, and CLI path containment per \u00a712.2. Commands `import-ontology` and `export --format zip` are registered in Phase 1 per the stub strategy resolved in OED-307 (see Decisions Deferred), since their underlying implementations are Phase 3 and Phase 4 deliverables respectively.",
            "scope": "minimal"
