        "instruction": "Encode four operator decisions from the kickoff synthesist's outstanding questions (task 005-roadmap-synthesize) into the project documents. Today is 2026-05-16.\n\nDecision Q1 \u2014 Excise SPEC \u00a731 item 14.\n- File: project/SPEC.md, section \"## 31. Definition of Done for v0.4 Engineering Baseline\"\n- Current item 14 verbatim: `14. Two compliant implementations produce byte-identical canonical and derived artifacts for the conformance fixtures.`\n- Action: REMOVE this line. Then RENUMBER items 15\u219214, 16\u219215, 17\u219216.\n- Rationale: The kgModeler POC (github.com/Skreen5hot/kgModeler) is not a v0.4-conformant implementation. GraphWrite is the sole v0.4 implementation. No second implementation is planned. DoD item 14 is unachievable as written.\n\nDecision Q2 \u2014 Phase 1 CLI stubs for Phase 3 / Phase 4 commands.\n- File: project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md, Phase 1 section\n- Add (or augment existing) explicit stub policy:\n  - `import-ontology` in Phase 1: exit code 2 with stderr \"not yet implemented; available in Phase 3\"\n  - `export --format zip` in Phase 1: exit code 2 with stderr \"not yet implemented; available in Phase 4\"\n- Phase 1 acceptance criteria should specify the stub behavior is correct (return code 2 + the documented stderr); don't require full implementation in Phase 1.\n\nDecision Q3 \u2014 Move OED-303 from Phase 3 to Phase 1 exit gate.\n- File: project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md\n- The Phase 1 OED gates list MUST include OED-303 as a Phase 1 exit gate.\n- The Phase 3 OED gates list MUST NO LONGER mention OED-303 as a Phase 3 exit gate (it's resolved before Phase 3 even starts now).\n- The Phase 1 golden-file note about \"ecm:validationReports: [] as a documented temporary assumption pending OED-303\" should be REPLACED with: \"ecm:validationReports retention policy implemented per OED-303 ruling\".\n- Section \"### 3.6 OED-303 Retention Policy Integration\" should be moved out of Phase 3 and placed inside Phase 1 (renamed to its appropriate Phase 1 section number).\n- OED table entry for OED-303: change \"Phase 3 exit gate\" to \"Phase 1 exit gate\".\n\nDecision Q4 \u2014 Create OED-313 for conformance fixture set.\n- File: project/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md\n- Add OED-313 to the OED table. Suggested row: `| OED-313 | 1, 4 | Phase 1 and Phase 4 exit gates | Open |`\n- Title / description for OED-313: \"Conformance fixture set \u2014 exact input fixture sets for Phase 1 vs Phase 4 golden files. Resolution required before any golden files are committed.\"\n- Phase 1 and Phase 4 acceptance criteria: where they currently say \"fixture set TBD\" or similar deferred-decision language, replace or augment to reference OED-313.\n\nDecision Q5 \u2014 DEFERRED \u2014 no action.\n\nOperator-record \u2014 File: project/DECISIONS.md\n- Append four new ADR entries (ADR-002 through ADR-005) at the end of the file using the EXISTING format (ADR-NNN: Title, Date 2026-05-16, Decision, Context, Consequences).\n- ADR-002: Excise SPEC \u00a731 item 14 \u2014 the \"second compliant implementation\" DoD requirement, since no second v0.4 implementation is planned.\n- ADR-003: Phase 1 stubs `import-ontology` and `export --format zip` with exit code 2 plus \"not yet implemented; available in Phase N\" stderr.\n- ADR-004: Move OED-303 (validation report retention policy) from Phase 3 exit gate to Phase 1 exit gate.\n- ADR-005: Create OED-313 to track the conformance fixture set decision as a Phase 1 and Phase 4 joint exit gate.\n\nOperator-record \u2014 File: project/ROADMAP.md\n- Phase 1 description should mention OED-303 and OED-313 are Phase 1 exit gates.\n- Phase 1 should note the CLI stubs for `import-ontology` and `export --format zip`.\n\nFor every change you propose:\n- `file`: relative path\n- `before`: exact current text snippet (a UNIQUE substring of the current file content, byte-identical including whitespace, newlines, and any unicode chars \u2014 em-dashes are `\u2014` U+2014, section 